document_title: Genital warts: Causes, signs, complications, prevention
subsection_content:
Genital warts, or genital warts, are a common sexually transmitted disease caused by a virus, manifested by soft warts on the genitals accompanied by pain and itching. snoring, discomfort. The virus that causes genital warts is Human Papillomavirus (HPV). (first)
Some people develop genital warts within a few weeks of infection, but in others it can take months or years. In fact, most cases of HPV infection are asymptomatic or undetected. The proportion of people with obvious symptoms is very low, only about 1-2% of cases. Therefore, it is difficult for patients to determine their condition and accidentally transmit the virus to others.
